<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="81" type="conservation status">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Conservation status in Cameroon.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="81">
<taxonomicName authorityName="G. Taylor, Bull. Brit. Mus. (Nat. Hist.) Bot. 1: 57" authorityYear="1953" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Podostemaceae" genus="Letestuella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Letestuella tisserantii" order="Malpighiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tisserantii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Letestuella tisserantii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is listed on http://www.iucnredlist.org as Least Concern (
<bibRefCitation author="Diop, FN" journalOrPublisher="Opera Botanica Belgica" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" refId="B25" refString="Diop, FN, 2010d. Letestuellatisserantii. The IUCN Red List of Threatened Species 2010: e.T185497A8422867. [Downloaded on 20 August 2018]" title="Letestuellatisserantii. The IUCN Red List of Threatened Species 2010: e. T 185497 A 8422867. [Downloaded on 20 August 2018]" year="2010 d">Diop 2010d</bibRefCitation>
) since it occurs in many countries. The taxon is known from two localities in Cameroon. The extent of occurrence is less than 100 km2, and the area of occupancy is less than 10 km2. Dams on the Sanaga River and agricultural activities are the main threats to the species. Based on the threats and the number of localities where the species is found, 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="L." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="L. tisserantii" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="tisserantii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">L. tisserantii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is here assessed as Endangered. IUNC Red List Category: 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Endangered ENB2ab (iii).</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
